@node "INTRO" "What this Program does..."
@{u}Introduction@{uu}

I have been using the new FAME-BBS System for about 1 year now, and as
you all know validating New Users etc is a normal job.  If you only have
to validate one user and nothing more, it can be very cumbersome to enter
the BBS only for validation purposes.  So I decided to write my own
external User-Editor, allowing me to work on any user without going into
my BBS first.

The decision to use MUI was simple, I don't like hardcoded programs, which
don't allow you to configure the Program-Outfit to use other fonts, other
images etc...  Well, MUI is the right solution for this problem, as it is
100% user-configurable.  On the other Hand, MUI allows the coders not to
spend most of the Development Time in creating a GUI, but in developing
the program itself.  Creating a MUI-Interface is sooo simple..it takes me
three days to create the whole GUI for User-Ed!!  So if you don't have
MUI or don't like it, sit down in front of your Computer and start
creating a standard GUI which looks familiar to the current GUI...happy
guruing...:) 
@endnode

@node "INSTALLATION" "How to install User-Editor"
@{b}Requirements@{ub}

 To use User-Ed, you need the following things:

 - OS 2.04 or higher

 - MUI V2.2 or higher, MUI 3 is recommended to use all new features!

 - Completely installed FAME-System

 - For localisation you need locale.library v38+ or higher, otherwise 
   the User-Editor uses the built-in English language.

@{b}Installation@{ub}

 When you first install the FAME-System, the User-Editor is copied into
 the FAME:Modules/ drawer.  Also this Location is the default path set in
 'SystemEditor/FAME Modules'.  If you don't like this location, you could
 of course copy it to another, but since all external FAME modules are
 stored inside this drawer, it's the best idea by far to have all files
 stored in the same place!

 If you receive an Update of the User-Editor, simply overwrite your
 existing version with the new one, and also update all other files
 supplied with the update archive of User-Editor.

 If you want to use the User-Editor in your preferred language, copy the
 catalog-file of your language (if supplied) into your locale:Catalogs/
 <language>/drawer.  If you have choosen to install User-Editor to a
 different drawer from the default drawer 'FAME:Modules/', please make
 sure that the path for User-Editor set in 'SystemEditor/FAME Modules'
 points to the correct path!

 That's all for installation, now have fun using the User-Editor!
@endnode

@node "START" "Startoptions from User-Editor"
@{b}How to start User-Ed@{ub}

User-Ed can be started in different ways:

 1. Starting via Double-Click on its icon.

 2. Starting from FAME-@{"Server" link "Server.guide/Main"}.
    
 3. Starting from CLI

When you start it from CLI, you *MUST* enter the BBS-Location as the first
argument!  So a valid call is:

                          USER-EDITOR FAME:

Another possible call is:
 
                          USER-EDITOR FAME: <USERNUM>

You don't have to specify the <USERNUM> argument, but if given,
User-Editor loads in the specified User after opening the Window.  

The same call also works from the FAME-@{"Server" link "Server.guide/Main"} when starting the
User-Editor from the Gadget UsEd (behind the Info-Gadget).  See the
@{"Server" link "Server.guide/Main"} Documentation for further information about the start-options of
the @{"Server" link "Server.guide/Main"}.

@endnode

