@node "MAIN_BUTTON_LOAD" "BUTTON: Load"

 @{u}Load User@{uu}

When selected, User-Ed first checks out if you've changed the current
user settings.  If you have, the User-Ed asks you if you want to lose
these alterations.  Now User-Ed opens a Window containing a ListView
Gadget with an alphabetical sorted list of all your users, including
inactive/deleted users.  User-Ed jumps automatically to the position of
your name in the List and activate the Listview-Cursor on it.  Now you
can choose which user is to be loaded by using the CURSOR keys and Enter
to select or by simply using the Mouse, or by pressing the LOAD
Button..:) You can abort this action by pressing the ABORT Button or the
Close Gadget.  (ESC also closes the Window; this works with any
MUI-Window!).

When selecting a user, User-Ed loads in the specific data and closes the
Listview-Window.  
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BUTTON_SAVE" "BUTTON: Save"

 @{u}Save User@{uu}

When selected, User-Ed saves the current user's data to your user.data
and user.keys .

Nothing more to say about it I think..:)
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BUTTON_REACTIVE" "BUTTON: Re-Active"

 @{u}Re-Active@{uu}

This Button sets the current user-status to Validated.  If you have a new
user, you could validate him (give him access) by pressing this button.
But you will have to set all the other settings for yourself, i.e.  the
access level, online time etc.

If this is too much work for you, try the @{"Presets" link "MAIN_BUTTON_PRESETS" 0} Button, which makes all
the settings automatically for you.

See also: @{"Inactive" link "MAIN_BUTTON_INACTIVE" 0}, @{"NewĀUser" link "MAIN_BUTTON_NEWUSER" 0}, @{"Delete" link "MAIN_BUTTON_DELETE" 0}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BUTTON_INACTIVE" "BUTTON: Inactive"

 @{u}Inactive@{uu}

This button switches current User's Status to Inactive.  In this Status,
the user-entry remains in your user.data, but the User itself is not able
to get into your BBS.  Good for users, which are i.e.  on holiday for a
few weeks, and don't want to get hacked...

See also: @{"Re-Activate" link "MAIN_BUTTON_REACTIVE" 0}, @{"NewĀUser" link "MAIN_BUTTON_NEWUSER" 0}, @{"Delete" link "MAIN_BUTTON_DELETE" 0}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BUTTON_NEWUSER" "BUTTON: New User"
 @{u}New User@{uu}

With this button you could set the current user as a New User.  In this
state, you have to @{"validate" link "MAIN_BUTTON_INACTIVE" 0} the user, otherwise he's not able to do much
on your BBS.

See also: @{"Re-Activate" link "MAIN_BUTTON_REACTIVE" 0}, @{"Delete" link "MAIN_BUTTON_DELETE" 0}, @{"Inactive" link "MAIN_BUTTON_INACTIVE" 0}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BUTTON_DELETE" "BUTTON: Delete"
 @{u}Delete@{uu}

By pressing this button, you set the current user's status to Deleted.  In
this state, the next New User who comes onto the BBS overwrites the deleted
account before the new user's data is appended to your user.data.  So you
can then be sure that you only have active or Inactive users in your
user.data, not deleted ones.

See also: @{"Re-Activate" link "MAIN_BUTTON_REACTIVE" 0}, @{"Inactive" link "MAIN_BUTTON_INACTIVE" 0}, @{"NewĀUser" link "MAIN_BUTTON_NEWUSER" 0}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BUTTON_PRESETS" "BUTTON: Presets"

@{u}Presets@{uu}

When you want to validate a user, but also set all the requirements for 
the validated account automatically, you can use this Preset-Option.  
When pressed, a new Window appears, which shows you the first preset.  
Here you see the following things:

ConfAlias, AccessLevel, Ratio, RatioType, UserFileBase, daily bytes/files
and time limit.

This are the fields in the user.data, which are set by the preset option.
You can choose the desired Preset by clicking on the CycleGadget PRESET.
FAME allows you to have a maximum of 10 different presets including one
Preset for NewUser settings, which are configurable via SystemEditor/
Access/Presets. Select the Preset you need and press the button 
@{"Set to User" link "PRESET_SETUSER" 0}.  This sets all fields to the 
values seen in the Preset-Window.  To abort press the CloseGadget of the 
Window or the Cancel button.

@{u}NOTE:@{uu} Don't forget to save the current user-settings when using the Preset-
      option!!! Otherwise you lose the settings.
@endnode

@node "BUTTON_PREVIOUS" "BUTTON: Previous User"

 @{u}Previous User@{uu}

When pressing this, User-Ed loads in the previous user.  If you have made
any changes to the current user's settings, User-Ed asks you to confirm the
loading or to firstly save the changed user's data.  When you reach the
first user in your user.data, a small infotext appears in all 
Status/Username displays to inform you that you have reached the 
beginning.

See also: @{"Next" link "BUTTON_NEXT" 0}, @{"First/LastĀUser" link "MENU3" 0}
@endnode

@node "BUTTON_NEXT" "BUTTON: Next User"

 @{u}Next User@{uu}

When pressing this, User-Ed loads in the next user.  If you have made any
changes to the current user's settings, User-Ed asks you to confirm the
loading or to firstly save the changed user's data.  When you reach the
last user in your user.data, a small infotext appears in all 
Status/Username displays to inform you that you have reached the end of 
the user.data.

See also: @{"Prev" link "BUTTON_PREVIOUS" 0}, @{"First/LastĀUser" link "MENU3" 0}
@endnode

@node "MAIN_BUTTON_QUIT" "BUTTON: Quit User-Ed"

 @{u}Quit@{uu}

Exit Program...what else..:)
@endnode

@node "MENU1" "MENU: Last/First User"

 @{u}First/Last User@{uu}

With these two menu-entries you can jump directly to the beginning/end of
your user.data.  This is useful if you have many users and want to view
only the last few users etc.  
@endnode

@node "PRESET_SETUSER" "Preset/BUTTON: Set to User"

No information available yet.

@endnode

